# Security response headers for the SPA + static assets (served by the Cloudflare assets binding).
# This file does NOT affect `vite dev` (it ships only with the built assets), so HMR's inline
# scripts are unaffected. The Worker routes (/api/*, /agents/*) return JSON/audio, not framed HTML,
# so the clickjacking/XSS surface is the SPA HTML this covers.
#
# CSP is scoped to exactly what the app loads: same-origin hashed JS/CSS bundles; Google Fonts
# (stylesheet from fonts.googleapis.com, font files from fonts.gstatic.com — see index.html);
# data: URIs for the inline SVG noise background (styles.css); blob: audio for the goblin TTS
# playback (useGoblinVoice.ts → new Audio(blobUrl)); same-origin connect for the API + the
# /agents/* WebSocket ('self' covers same-origin wss); and Cloudflare Web Analytics (the external
# static.cloudflareinsights.com beacon + its cloudflareinsights.com data POST).
#
# script-src is deliberately strict (no 'unsafe-inline'): the app ships no first-party inline
# scripts and renders every RAG answer/citation as escaped React text (no dangerouslySetInnerHTML,
# no markdown→HTML), so this is defense-in-depth against a *future* injection sink, not the primary
# XSS control. It costs nothing here (same-origin hashed bundles) and avoids the grade Mozilla
# Observatory docks for 'unsafe-inline' in script-src.
#
# Cloudflare Bot Fight Mode (on at the zone) injects a per-request inline bootstrap loading
# /cdn-cgi/challenge-platform/scripts/jsd/main.js (JS Detections). Its r/t params change every
# request, so it is UNHASHABLE, and this CSP blocks it BY DESIGN — one benign console error. That
# is harmless: on the free plan JS Detections is a passive fingerprint signal Cloudflare never
# enforces on (enforcement needs Enterprise Bot Management), and BFM's actual protection is an edge
# CPU-challenge that runs before the Worker regardless. Free BFM cannot disable JS Detections, so the
# only ways to silence the console are a per-request nonce (CSP moved into the Worker, which then
# stamps the same nonce onto Cloudflare's injected script) or 'unsafe-inline' (NO — it reopens the
# inline-script XSS class). We accept the cosmetic console error and keep the strict policy.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com https://app.skopia.dev; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data:; media-src 'self' blob:; connect-src 'self' https://cloudflareinsights.com https://app.skopia.dev; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'
